Class TransferToOfflineWizard

java.lang.Object
  oracle.ide.wizard.Wizard
      oracle.apps.fnd.applxdf.jdev.dboffline.wizards.TransferToOfflineWizard
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.EventListener, oracle.ide.panels.CommitListener
public class TransferToOfflineWizard
extends oracle.ide.wizard.Wizard
implements oracle.ide.panels.CommitListener

SQL Generated from Offline Database Objects. 

 (Generate)

     * Step 1 Specify source
           o Online location + schema
     * Step 2 Specify target
           o Offline location
     * Step 3 Object picker
           o SelectDBObjectsPanel
     * Step 4 Choose Operation
           o Choose Operation Full wizard flavor
           o Choose Operation Full wizard flavor plus connection list box
     * Step 5 Manual Reconcile (Optional)
       see cm.dt.ui.reconcile.reconcilePanel
     * Step 6 SQL Script Options
       see jdevimpl.offlinedb.panels.GenerateSQLPanel
       moved to db-online jdeveloper.cm.dt.ui.gen
     * Finish
           o Summary
           o Any TraversablePanels registered with Provider
 <\pre>

invokeImportWizard


public boolean invokeImportWizard(java.lang.String sourceConnectionName,
                                  oracle.javatools.db.DBObjectProvider pro,
                                  oracle.javatools.db.SchemaObject[] selectedObjs)




Invokes the generate wizard. This can be used by the modelers or anyone
 else wanting to fire off the wizard for themselves without a Context.
 The selected objects are a pre-selection - the user can still alter that
 choice and select their own objects.
